  "market_context": "Light Crude Oil Futures (CL1!) on 2 February 2024. London session sweeps low-resistance liquidity to the upside with a series of up-close candles, forming a reversal. Bias is bearish continuation lower into New York session.",
  "key_observation": "At 08:30 NY open, price manipulates downward (opposite of the expected upward manipulation), signaling a retracement back into London's prior range rather than immediate continuation lower. The analyst uses this retracement as the short entry zone, with continuation lower confirmed at 10:00 AM.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified that during London session, price ran low-resistance liquidity to the upside, forming a series of up-close candles into a swing high.",
    "Step 2: Marked the Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH) where price closed below the series of up-close candles, confirming a London reversal and establishing a bearish bias.",
    "Step 3: Noted that while a London entry was possible on the CHoCH, the analyst focuses on New York session and waited for the 08:30 time level.",
    "Step 4: Observed that at 08:30, price manipulated downward (opposing the expected upward manipulation for a bearish continuation), interpreting this as a retracement signal back into London's prior range.",
    "Step 5: Identified the retracement back into London's range as the short entry zone, entering a short position within that prior consolidation area.",
    "Step 6: Set the stop-loss above the 08:30 opposing (downward) manipulation run.",
    "Step 7: Targeted 2R to the downside, with continuation lower confirmed at 10:00 AM (aligned with the 4-hour open high-low-close reference level)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached 2R target; price continued lower at 10:00 AM, confirming the London Reversal / New York retracement continuation profile.",
  "lessons": "When 08:30 NY open moves opposite to the expected manipulation direction, treat it as a retracement into London's range rather than a failed setup. Use that retracement as the short entry, with the stop above the 08:30 run and a 2R target at the 10:00 AM or 4-hour open level.",
